items.title: Timor-Leste scraps lifetime pensions after student-led protests
items.summary: Timor-Leste votes to cancel the lifetime pension law for MPs and public officials, following student-led demonstrations against lavish perks in one of South-East Asia's poorest countries.

items.title: Baby koala rides golden retriever like a racehorse in south-west Victoria
items.summary: When Steve Lamplough heard a commotion outside his south-west Victorian home, the last thing he expected to see was a joey koala riding his dog like a racehorse.

items.title: Geoff Ayling, composer of some of Australia's most recognised ad jingles, dies

items.title: Marion, Burnside and West Lakes among shopping centres listed by SA Police as Declared Public Precincts
items.summary: SA Police has announced Declared Public Precincts at eight shopping centres in metropolitan Adelaide, which will allow police to search people and remove them from the site.

items.title: Australian doctors become unofficial correspondents from hospital in Gaza City
items.summary: In a ruined hospital and with little medication, two Australian doctors say the situation inside Gaza City is a "nightmare".

items.title: TASC 'confident' Tasmanian school exams are ready after report finds 11 errors last year

items.title: Daytime clubbing grows in popularity as dance venues cater to older patrons
